    "http://schema.org/url": [
      {
        "@id": "https://ww3.ticketpro.ca/event.php?event_id=10758"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/name": [
      {
        "@value": "Songs & Stories - Jim Henman, Dave Carroll, Lisa Richard"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/description": [
      {
        "@value": "<p>Sit back and enjoy a night of unforgettable stories and songs. This intimate and powerful showcase combines the distinct voices, talents,  and experiences of three incredible songwriters, making it a truly one-of-a-kind performance. </p>\n\n<p>The trio has already received overwhelming praise, with multiple sold-out shows at venues like The Carleton, The Sanctuary Arts Centre, and The Wellington Fletcher Lakehouse.</p>\n\n<p>This extraordinary lineup offers a blend of talent, storytelling, and musical mastery that promises to captivate an audience:<br>\n•      Jim Henman: An original member of the iconic band April Wine and an inductee into Canada's Songwriting Hall of Fame, Jim's deep roots in Canadian music and storytelling resonate with fans of all generations.<br>\n•      Dave Carroll: Known worldwide for his viral sensation 'United Breaks Guitars' (over 30 million views on YouTube), Dave has graced platforms like The Ellen DeGeneres Show and garnered numerous songwriting nominations, including an East Coast Music Award. <br>\n•      Lisa Richard: Celebrated for her breathtaking performance with Vince Gill and The Time Jumpers in Nashville, Lisa continues to charm audiences with her heartfelt tributes, such as her rendition of Gordon Lightfoot's 'If You Could Read My Mind.' She has won two independent international songwriting awards, two Music Nova Scotia nominations and continues to earn accolades for her artistry.<br>\n•      Joining the trio on stage is special guest master guitarist Warren Robert. </p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n"
      }
    ],
