    ],
    "http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#wasDerivedFrom": [
      {
        "@id": "https://ww3.ticketpro.ca/event.php?event_id=10867"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/url": [
      {
        "@id": "https://ww3.ticketpro.ca/event.php?event_id=10867"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/name": [
      {
        "@value": "Readings by Mark Critch & Elizabeth Murphy - Writers at Woody Point 2026"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/description": [
      {
        "@value": "<p>The Writers at Woody Point Festival returns August 18-23, 2026, bringing its signature blend of music, literature, and community to the historic Woody Point Heritage Theatre and venues throughout the town of Woody Point. Now in its 23rd year, the festival continues to offer a vibrant and eclectic mix of celebrated and emerging voices, all set against the stunning backdrop of Gros Morne National Park.</p>\n\n<p>This year's lineup combines beloved festival alumni and exciting newcomers — internationally acclaimed authors, some of Canada's bestselling writers, and outstanding musical guests performing across a week of unforgettable evenings. Expect rich storytelling, live music, and that singular August magic Woody Point is known for.</p>\n\n<p>'Writers at Woody Point may be, pound for pound, the best literary festival in the world' — Wayne Johnston</p>\n\n<p>Featured Writers: Richard Ford, Miriam Toews, Donna Morrissey, Ian Williams, Anita Rau Badami, Mark Critch, Mary Walsh, Elizabeth Murphy, Diedre Halbot, and David Ferry.</p>\n\n<p>Musical Guests: Sarah Harmer, R Sheaves, Adrian Sutherland, Christine Fellows, The East Pointers, Sweet William Society, Des Walsh, RASA, Hit Piece, and Duane Andrews and The Hot Club of Conception Bay.</p.\n\n<p>Festival Hosts: Tom Power, Elamin Abdelmahmoud, and Angela Antle</p>\n\n<p>2026 Poster Artist: Ned Pratt.</p>\n\n<p>From literary readings paired with live music, to stand-alone concerts, intimate interviews, coffee conversations, outdoor hikes, and lively late-night sessions, the festival offers a week-long celebration of storytelling, place, and creative connection. Stay tuned for further artist and programming announcements as summer approaches.</p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>No festival passes - all events are ticketed individually.</li>\n<li>Limit of four (4) tickets per customer per event.</li>\n<li>Remaining tickets, if available, will be sold at the door prior to showtime.</li></ul>\n\n<p>Writers at Woody Point is proudly supported by presenting sponsor BMO Bank of Montreal, and funded by ArtsNL - Newfoundland and Labrador Arts Council, Canada Council for the Arts, the Government of Canada (Canadian Heritage, ACOA Atlantic Opportunities Agency, and Canada Summer Jobs), and the Government of Newfoundland and Labrador - Cultural Economic Development Program.</p>\n\n<p>Event and venue partners include Qalipu First Nation, The Merchant Warehouse, Royal Canadian Legion, Parks Canada, Lawnya Vawnya, Shoal Brook United Church, Galliott Studios, Woody Point Public Library, Blue Heron Books, the Town of Woody Point, and Gros Morne Coffee Roasters.</p>\n\n<p>Find lineup, event, ticket and visitation details here: <a href='http://www.writersatwoodypoint.com/' target='_blank'>www.writersatwoodypoint.com</a></p>\n\n<style>\n.filter-page-show-temp {\ndisplay: block !important \n}\n</style>\n"
      }
    ],
